{
  "version": 1,
  "tasks": [
    {
      "id": "RQ-0085",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Guard queue-only agent commands against stray edits",
      "description": "Runner-backed queue-shaping commands tell agents to modify only the queue, but the command implementations trust successful runner exits and valid queue JSON rather than enforcing a post-run mutation boundary. A scan or task-builder runner can accidentally edit source, docs, or config files and still succeed if the queue validates. Add a shared post-run guard for queue-only workflows so CueLoop either rejects/reverts unexpected non-queue mutations or reports an explicit operator decision before persisting backfilled queue fields.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "scan",
        "safety",
        "queue",
        "runner",
        "agent-docs"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/cueloop/src/commands/scan.rs",
        "crates/cueloop/src/commands/task/build.rs",
        "crates/cueloop/src/commands/task/update/runner.rs",
        "crates/cueloop/src/commands/task/decompose/planning.rs",
        "crates/cueloop/src/git/clean.rs or equivalent git cleanliness helper",
        "crates/cueloop/assets/prompts/scan_general_v2.md",
        "crates/cueloop/assets/prompts/scan_maintenance_v2.md",
        "crates/cueloop/assets/prompts/task_builder.md",
        "crates/cueloop/tests/",
        "cueloop queue validate"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: crates/cueloop/assets/prompts/scan_general_v2.md :: Outcome Contract :: scan agents are told success means only `{{config.queue.file}}` is modified and queue validation passes.",
        "path: crates/cueloop/assets/prompts/task_builder.md :: Output Target :: task-builder agents are told to modify `{{config.queue.file}}` only and no other files.",
        "path: crates/cueloop/src/commands/scan.rs :: run_scan :: pre-run cleanliness is checked with `git::require_clean_repo_ignoring_paths`, then runner execution uses `revert_on_error: true`, but the success path only validates queue state, backfills new task fields, and saves the queue; it does not reject unexpected source/docs/config edits after a successful runner run.",
        "path: crates/cueloop/src/commands/task/build.rs :: build_task_impl :: runner-backed task creation validates queue state before/after and saves backfilled fields, but it does not run a clean-repo preflight or post-run allowed-path check even though its prompt says queue-only output.",
        "path: crates/cueloop/src/runutil/execution/orchestration/core.rs :: run_prompt_with_handling_backend :: revert handling is only applied on interrupted, timeout, non-zero, signal, or other failure paths; successful runner output returns without any mutation-boundary check."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Define the canonical allowed mutation set for queue-only runner commands: active queue, done archive when applicable, and any intentional CueLoop cache/checkpoint outputs; exclude source, docs, configs, and prompts by default.",
        "Add a shared post-run cleanliness helper that compares the clean pre-run baseline with current git status and reports unexpected paths with enough detail for humans and machine callers.",
        "Wire the guard into scan, task build, task update, and task decomposition planning/write paths where prompts or docs promise queue-only behavior, without breaking legitimate queue/cache backfills.",
        "Decide and implement safe handling for unexpected edits: fail before queue backfill/save when possible, and use the existing revert/keep decision path when runner output already changed the workspace.",
        "Add integration tests using a fake runner that edits both `.cueloop/queue.jsonc` and an unrelated source/doc file; assert the command does not silently succeed and that the queue remains valid or is restored according to the chosen policy.",
        "Verify with focused command tests, representative prompt rendering tests, `cueloop scan --help`, `cueloop task --help`, and `cueloop queue validate`."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan: post-0.4.1 release dogfood scan",
      "created_at": "2026-05-03T17:51:11Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-05-03T17:51:11Z",
