    {
      "id": "RQ-0087",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Remove misleading release-dry-run mutation path",
      "description": "The Makefile still exposes `make release-dry-run`, but that target runs the same `scripts/release.sh verify` transaction as `make release-verify`. Verify intentionally syncs versions, promotes the changelog, runs release gates, builds artifacts, and records a release snapshot, leaving release metadata dirty until execute commits it. A target named dry-run is a trap for agents and maintainers because it sounds non-mutating. Rename, remove, or change the target so the command name and help text match the transaction's real side effects.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "scan",
        "release",
        "workflow",
        "docs",
        "automation"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "Makefile",
        "mk/rust.mk",
        "scripts/release.sh",
        "scripts/lib/release_verify_pipeline.sh",
        "docs/guides/release-runbook.md",
        "docs/releasing.md",
        "crates/cueloop/tests/release_script_help_test.rs",
        "crates/cueloop/tests/release_integration_contract_test/",
        "make help",
        "make release-verify VERSION=<version>",
        "cueloop queue validate"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: mk/rust.mk :: release-dry-run target :: `make release-dry-run VERSION=x.y.z` invokes `scripts/release.sh verify \"$(VERSION)\"`, the same release verification transaction used by `make release-verify`.",
        "path: scripts/lib/release_verify_pipeline.sh :: release_prepare_verified_snapshot :: verify mode runs `versioning.sh sync --version`, `release_generate_changelog_entries`, `release_promote_changelog`, `pre-public-check --release-context`, `release_run_ship_gate`, `build-release-artifacts.sh`, `release_generate_release_notes`, and records the ready snapshot.",
        "path: docs/guides/release-runbook.md :: Notes :: a successful `make release-verify` intentionally leaves release metadata dirty until `make release` turns it into the release commit.",
        "path: Makefile :: help target :: help advertises `make release-verify VERSION=x.y.z` but does not explain `release-dry-run`, leaving the mutating alias discoverable only from target names and scripts.",
        "path: crates/cueloop/tests/release_script_help_test.rs :: release script help coverage :: tests assert the transaction command model for `verify`, `execute`, and `reconcile`, but there is no contract test preventing Makefile aliases from presenting verify as a non-mutating dry run."
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Choose the safest cutover: remove `release-dry-run`, make it a pure preview that never mutates tracked files, or turn it into a deprecated alias that prints an explicit mutation warning and points to `release-verify`.",
        "Update Makefile help, release docs, and any script references so there is only one clear source of truth for the mutating verification transaction.",
        "If the target remains, add a prominent help line and preflight output stating that it prepares a release snapshot and intentionally dirties release metadata.",
        "Add Makefile/release contract tests that assert mutating release verification is not exposed under a misleading dry-run name without a warning.",
        "Verify with `make help`, release script help tests, targeted release policy tests, and `cueloop queue validate`."
      ],
      "notes": [],
      "request": "scan: post-0.4.1 release dogfood scan",
      "created_at": "2026-05-03T17:51:11Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-05-03T17:51:11Z",
